<recipe>
    <name>Coconut-Pecan Frosting</name>
    <indexCharacter>c</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>Beat egg yolks, milk and vanilla in a large saucepan with wire whisk until well blended. Add sugar and butter; cook on medium heat 12 min. or until thickened and golden brown, stirring constantly. Remove from heat.

Add coconut and nuts; mix well. Cool to desired spreading consistency. Use to frost your favorite cake or cupcake recipe. Makes about 4-1/2 cups or 36 servings, 2 Tbsp. each

Note:
Makes enough to frost top and sides of 3 (8 or 9-inch) cake layers, tops of 2 (13x9-inch) cakes or 36 cupcakes.</instructions>
